def: A kind of amaranth (Amarantus caudatus). Dr. Prior.
The point of junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures ofthe skull.
A contrary method of procedure; opposite course of action.
Any of the live stock found in a region, as distinguished fromsuch as belong to pure and distinct imported breeds. [U.S.]
Mirror-faced; reflecting the sentiments of another. [R.] "Theglass-faced flatterer." Shak.
To quicken; to make alive. [Obs.] Dr. H. More.

One of that class of Calvinists who believed that God's decreeof election determined that man should fall, in order that theopportunity might be furnished of securing the redemption of a partof the race, the decree of salvation being conceived of as formedbefore or beyond, and not after or following, the lapse, or fall. Cf.Infralapsarian.
